  "guided": true,
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Now we leave the home row for the first time and reach up to the top row. R and U are the first stops, and the same trusty index fingers do the work. Up is a longer move than sideways, so take it slowly until the hand learns the distance."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "R sits directly above F, so the left index reaches up for it. U sits directly above J, so the right index reaches up for that. Keep the other fingers resting at home while the index makes the trip - that anchor is what tells your hand how far up to go."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "⬆️",
      "title": "Up, then snap back",
      "text": "The reach up is the easy half. The discipline is the return: the moment you have pressed R or U, snap the index finger back down to F or J. Lose the anchor and the next letter turns into a guess - and a guess, on deadline, is how typos get printed."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "r",
      "baseReps": 20,
      "keys": ["r"],
      "target": "r r r r r r r r r r r r r r r r r r r r",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Letter R",
      "hint": "Left index reaches up to R (above F), then back to F. One space after each."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "u",
      "baseReps": 20,
      "keys": ["u"],
      "target": "u u u u u u u u u u u u u u u u u u u u",
      "finger": "indigo",
      "title": "Letter U",
      "hint": "Right index reaches up to U (above J), then back to J. One space after each."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "r u",
      "baseReps": 10,
      "keys": ["r", "u"],
      "target": "r u r u r u r u r u r u r u r u r u r u",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Alternate",
      "hint": "Alternate the index fingers up: r - u - r - u. One space after each."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Two new letters, and the vocabulary opens up. These are real words now - read each one whole, then type it at an even pace, letting the index finger travel up and home for every R and U."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "Don't look down. The moment your eyes drop to the keys, the thought you were chasing slips away.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
